{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"enginous-brainless-cranefly","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Description\nWire the code_health metric specs to read from the analyzer (LOC/complexity/duplication) instead of scanning `src/rebar/**/*.py` and `.github/module-size-limit.txt`. Re-express the module-size cap as an OPTIONAL policy layered on the analyzer LOC signal (from config), and make a missing/unconfigured analyzer render honest Unavailable — killing the fabricated-zeros failure mode. Does NOT touch the CI module-size *gate* (separate governance).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] module_size_distribution / oversized_module_count / module_size_trend read via the analyzer; no `src/rebar` or `.github/module-size-limit.txt` reference remains in the metric readers.\n- [ ] Module-size cap comes from `[code_health]` config as an optional policy over the LOC signal (not hardcoded).\n- [ ] No analyzer configured -> Unavailable (regression test asserts NO {count:0,max_loc:0} authoritative value and NO leaked errno reason).\n- [ ] git-delta readers (churn/refactor_ratio) unchanged; agent_process metrics unchanged.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Regression test reproducing the audit finding (foreign repo -> honest Unavailable, not fabricated zeros).\n- [ ] Full `rebar metrics` run in-repo still green for unaffected metrics.\n\n## Dependencies: Children 4, 5, 6\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py, src/rebar/metrics/registry.py (seeds), src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py, tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py\n## Estimated scope: M (3-4 files)","id":"0734-ceae-be55-4fa7","parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Migrate code_health readers onto the analyzer; drop hardcoded src/rebar + module-size cap file"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784517472580923001,"uuid":"5b29527a-7c60-457f-a588-6cad62ca4189"}